result.execSummary:
The defendant Kristina Ann Fiebrink was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 2nd-Degree Recklessly Endangering Safety, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.30(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Consecutive to: CONSECUTIVE to any other time being served with credit for 3 days served.
Same conditions as probation except for condition time.

miscConds.notes:
Provide DNA sample if one has not already been provided- pay surcharge.
Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs.
The Court ordered that all financial obligations and/or restitution be paid during the period of probation, and if revoked, through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.
Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment.

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon she may never possess a firearm.  Court advised defendant that her voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until her civil rights are restored.

No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause.
No drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses).

Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent.
Mental health assessment and any follow-up care and or treatment.
Take all medications as prescribed, in the manner prescribed, and as prescribed by a treating physician.
Participate in a Cognitive Thinking program.

Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzer tests.
Obtain AODA assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment.

timeConds.notes: No electronic monitoring. No good time credit. Court will allow for release to the Day Reporting Center for programming.

Defendant Kristina Ann Fiebrink in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  Defendant Kristina Ann Fiebrink in custody.  Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Negotiations placed on the record.   Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered Counts 2 and 3, as well as case #14CM2978 and case #13CM4874 dismissed and read-in to case for the purposes of sentencing. 

As to Count 1:  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon she may never possess a firearm.  Court advised defendant that her voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until her civil rights are restored.
